	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Providence</placeName> <date>Sunday</date> Morning</p>
				<p><date>November 30&#44; 1859</date>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Mr Editor</p>
				<p>Knowing that you are interested<lb/> in the welfare of the <sic>hebrew</sic> congregations through<lb/>out the <placeName>United States</placeName>&#44; and <sic>allways</sic><lb/> ready&#44; to insert in your valuable<lb/> Paper all facts concerning our<lb/> holy Religion&#44; I take pleasure<lb/> of informing you of the following<lb/> <del>facts</del> About two years ago <persName>Mr<lb/> A. Wormser</persName> <sic>than</sic> a resident of<lb/> this city&#44; has at that time remo<lb/>ved with his family to <placeName>New York</placeName>&#44;<lb/> and from that city left for <placeName>Uropa<add>&#63;</add></placeName><lb/> to <del>get</del> see those that where dear<lb/> to him&#44; and on saying good <sic>by</sic><lb/> to his Brethren of the congregation<lb/> San<add>&#63;</add> of Israel <sic>hi</sic> promised&#44; if<lb/> his life was spared to return in<lb/> <sic>safty</sic> to this country&#44; <sic>hi</sic> would</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>give as a donation to the Syna<lb/>goge a Favor&#44; his promise is<lb/> <sic>fullfilled</sic> for on <date>Sunday the 27<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> inst<lb/> <del>and by previous writing</del><lb/> <sic>hi</sic> presented to ex President <persName>Mr<lb/> B. Shuman</persName> in the <sic>Synagoge</sic> a<lb/> handsome favor <persName>Mr Wormser</persName><lb/> addressed the President very fluently<lb/> the President <sic>than</sic> thanked <persName>Mr Wormser</persName><lb/> in <sic>behalve</sic> of the members of the<lb/> congregation Sons of Israel&#44;<lb/> and accepted that valuable gift<lb/> and as <sic>hi</sic> addressed <persName>Mr Wormser</persName>&#44;<lb/> all eyes <sic>where</sic> full of tears&#44; and<lb/> all felt that such a gift must<lb/> be <sic>recordet</sic> above&#44; in the great<lb/> Book of Life&#44; after the ceremonies<lb/> the President called a meeting and<lb/> it was unanimously resolved<lb/> that <persName>Mr A Wormser</persName> be elected<lb/> a <sic>honerary</sic> member.  It was then<lb/> moved and carried <persName>Mr Wormsers</persName><lb/> name be <sic>instered</sic> on the regular</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>List&#44; and that his Name may be<lb/> mentioned at each prayer the<lb/> meeting <sic>than</sic> adjourned&#44; and<lb/> the President invited the Ladies<lb/> and Gentlemen to the honor<lb/> of <persName>Mr Joseph Stern</persName> to a<lb/> repast prepared for this ocas<lb/>sion&#44; ample justice was done<lb/> to all eatables&#44; and the company<lb/> brook<add>&#63;</add> up much pleased.</p>
				<p>Mr Editor</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">You please insert the<lb/> above as an editorial and<lb/> send your Bill for payment.</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Yours</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">A Goldsmith</persName> Sec.</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">Per B D</p>
		</body>
